notes: 12th Men: SCG MacGill (Aus) and Shoaib Malik (Pak)

Early rain postponed the match to start at 12:30pm, originally sheduled to start at 10am. The match was reduced to 41 overs-a-side, the fielding restrictions to apply for the first 12 overs, with 1 bowler permitted to bowl 9 overs and 4 bowlers to bowl 8 overs.

milestones.description: Wasim Akram has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (284) for PAK, going past Saleem Malik

stories.title: Steve Waugh guides Australia to comfortable win
stories.summary:
In a tournament already loaded with low scoring matches, and in a
season dominated by Australian wins, there came another contest at the
Melbourne Cricket Ground today to reinforce the pattern
